<TEXT>
the merce cunningham dance company celebrating 
its 35th anniversary with its longest new york engagement four 
weeks presented a premiere by cunningham on wednesday night 
the dance at the joyce theater for 11 dancers is titled 
eleven the music by robert ashley his first for the company 
is titled problems in the flying saucer the dance does not act 
that out 
as always with cunningham the dancers are proficient and 
fluidly graceful they shift weight and hold poses without 
stiffness a viewer may not know why one set of moves follows 
another but the dancers are entirely purposeful in performing them 
cunningham choreographs to use the entire stage giving his 
dancers the look of freedom a couple dancing together may not 
touch often but they stay in each others general area circles are 
negotiated slowly or spun with arms swinging broadly often one leg 
is extended while a dancers body turns profile then turns again 
to face the audience 
once a woman dancers enters walking with bent knees its 
amusing because its so different from the expansive movements that 
other dancers on stage at that moment are doing 
the music is two men talking michael pugliese with a 
french accent and takehisa kosugi in a near monotone kosugi 
composed the music for the other two dances on the evenings 
program doubles and grange eve cunningham danced in 
grange eve 
pugliese speaks first saying a sentence fragment like there 
is no sound or off in the daytime before he finishes a 
phrase kosugi comes in on top of it saying something like the 
south of france even if one listens only to one speaker phrases 
dont add up to sentences and not all words can be understood 
there are many pauses between sets of phrases since cunningham 
choreographs without music anyway the dance flows on 
program notes explain that ashleys work is an excerpt from a 
screenplay for an opera odalisque in which a lieutenant in a 
flying saucer explains to his captain something about a musician 
they have on board the cunningham dance foundation commissioned 
this arrangement and instructions for performance 
the present season which ends march 27 also includes the new 
york premiere of carousal done last summer at the jacobs 
pillow dance festival a revival of the 1968 rainforest and 
septet which cunningham created in 1953 his companys first 
year septet is danced to satie music it was revived last year 
after a 23year absence from the repertory 
after the joyce season the company will dance in san paolo rio 
de janeiro and belo horizonte brazil from april 8 through 15 
starting june 4 it will play seven german cities in two weeks 
including presenting a premiere commissioned by the berlin festival 
another dance will premiere at the avignon france festival 
between july 30 and aug 3 us summer dates include july 21 
through 23 at the american dance festival in durham nc and aug 
22 through 27 at saratoga springs ny 
</TEXT>
