plan to impose the contract but he said if attendants decide to 
strike the airline is prepared to hire permanent replacements 
theyre on a collision course and everybodys going to get 
hurt william genoese director of the teamsters airline division 
and the flight attendants chief negotiator told wccotv wednesday 
when asked what the chances of a strike next week are genoese 
said i would say theyre pretty close to 100 percent i would 
say unless somebody gets the people to the bargaining table the 
companys the one thats going to hurt itself 
teamsters have called a strategy meeting monday in washington 
dc for local union officers and strike captains at northwest he 
said 
the main obstacle to reaching a settlement between the airline 
and the flight attendants has been disagreement over how to raise 
lowerpaid bscale attendants to higher paid ascale wages 
northwest has proposed extending the bscale from five years to 
eight years meaning lowerwage flight attendants would have to 
wait an additional three years before earning topscale wages 
erskine said 
bscale flight attendants have said the airline is trying to 
break a promise that they would earn ascale wages after five years 
the union also has objected to twotier wage agreements saying 
they pit junior workers against senior workers 
the issue has intensified since northwest acquired republic 
airlines in 1986 roughly onethird of the 2600 former republic 
attendants work for bscale wages and the other twothirds have 
said they wouldnt get enough out of northwests latest wage offer 
under the contract proposal that will be implemented the 
entrylevel wage will go from more than 13000 a year to 15000 a 
year and the top base wage will go from the current 32000 up to 
35000 a year erskine said 
our door of course will always be open for further 
collective bargaining erskine said 
