<TEXT>
the national assembly today 
unanimously reelected president suharto but a military general 
angrily protested the selection process for vice president in which 
a suharto aide is favored 
the peoples consultative assembly reelected suharto the only 
presidential candidate to a fifth fiveyear term suharto 66 has 
led the nation of 170 million people since 1967 his reelection 
indicates he is in firm control of the island republic and its 
400000member armed forces 
the 1000member assembly the nations highest policymaking 
body meets every five years to choose the president and vice 
president and issue new guidelines for state policy 
state secretary sudharmono one of suhartos most trusted aides 
was expected to be elected vice president on friday the 11th and 
final day of the assembly session sudharmono 61 chairs the 
governing golkar party 
military sources who spoke on condition of anonymity said the 
army was opposed to sudharmonos nomination and wanted the newly 
appointed armed forces commander gen try sutrisno 52 to fill 
the post 
the opposition moslem united development party nominated its 
chairman jailani nario 59 for vice president 
shortly after suhartos reelection a military general sprang 
to the podium to charge the selection process for vice president 
was unfair 
brig gen ibrahim saleh of the governmentnominated military 
faction grabbed the microphone at the podium and said 
we indonesian soldiers who believe in god and defend honesty 
and justice have heard rumors saying that the nomination of the 
vice president is not being fairly and correctly carried out 
saleh said there are certain things that we feel are against 
our conscience he did not elaborate 
saleh was shouted down and later taken away by fellow officers 
and wang suwandi secretarygeneral of the national assembly 
later the commander of the powerful national security agency 
gen benny murdani told reporters that salehs statement did not 
represent the official view of the armed forces and that he was 
speaking for himself 
suharto was not present during the session 
suharto came to power following a 1965 communist coup attempt in 
which six army generals were killed before the challenge was 
smashed by forces he then led as commander of the army strategic 
command 
suharto is expected to form a new cabinet later this month that 
will have to tackle urgent problems of economic development 
including how to cope with a 421 billion foreign debt 
indonesias economy was hit hard in the last five years by 
economic recession and a sharp drop in the price of oil a major 
foreign exchange earner the country has to set aside 64 billion 
nearly a third of its annual budget to pay its loan 
installments for the fiscal year beginning in april 
the peoples consultative assembly is comprised of a 500member 
parliament and 500 provincial and district officials 
in elections last april the golkar party won 299 seats in 
parliament which also has 100 governmentnominated members from 
the military the moslem united development party has 63 seats and 
the indonesian democratic party 38 seats 
in the assembly golkar has 548 seats as well as 151 
governmentnominated members from the military and 147 from the 
provinces the moslem united development party has 93 and the 
indonesian democratic party 61 
</TEXT>
