<TEXT>
three men in a flatbed truck today smashed through 
steel barricades blocking glienicker bridge in communist east 
germany and roared over the bridge of spies into west berlin 
police said 
the dramatic escape across the bridge made famous by numerous 
eastwest spy exchanges over the years occurred shortly before 
dawn said a west berlin police spokesman 
police at the scene said the 7ton truck was loaded with empty 
propane gas tanks in an attempt to discourage border guards from 
firing their weapons 
the east german border police apparently did not open fire and 
the three men fled uninjured said a police spokesman who spoke on 
condition of anonymity 
the truck crashed through two steel gates and an electrified 
fence on the east german side raced across the bridge and smashed 
through another control gate in west berlin police said 
glienicker bridge connects potsdam east germany with west 
berlin potsdam is on berlins southwest outskirts 
the three men two of them age 37 and the other 27 then 
reported to west berlin police 
among the most famous swaps on glienicker bridge was the feb 
10 1962 exchange by the united states of convicted soviet kgb 
master spy col rudolph abel for francis gary powers whose u2 
surveillance plane was shot down over the soviet union 
