arab rioters shouting slaughter the jews and god is great 
fearing the arabs wanted to attack their homes some settlers said 
they rushed into the streets of hebron and fired warning shots 
the army said the violence by arabs was aimed only at the 
military 
arab residents said they were awakened at about midnight by 
carloads of settlers raiding their neighborhoods 
all the city was sleeping nobody was in the streets 
mustafa natsche the former mayor told the associated press it 
was a dreadful night there was a sort of battle under the windows 
of my house shooting crying moaning 
he said the arabs responded to the attack by throwing rocks at 
the settlers and israeli troops who arrived 
but rabbi moshe levinger told the ap they the arabs ran 
down near the synagogue they wanted to enter jewish homes they 
carried stones we responded by throwing stones and firing in the 
air 
the area military commander disputed levingers claim 
its important to stress that the riots were directed at the 
army and at no stage was there an intention or attempt to attack 
jewish homes the commander said on israel radio he did not give 
his name in keeping with military regulations 
an ap reporter saw dozens of vandalized arab cars including a 
station wagon with all its windows broken arab residents showed 
several revolver cartridges they collected after the clash and said 
they turned over nearly 100 to the israeli authorities as evidence 
levinger who has lived in hebron nine years is one of the 
founders of the 40family beit hadassah settlement inside the 
predominantly arab city of 50000 there is a second jewish enclave 
in hebron the hillside neighborhood of tel rumayda 
levinger claimed 500 arabs were involved in the rioting and came 
to within about 100 yards of jewish homes he said about 50 
settlers defended the homes 
if we hadnt stopped them there would have been a 
slaughter of jews men women and children levinger said 
but natsche and other arab witnesses said the clashes occured 
without provocation in arab neighborhoods several miles from jewish 
homes 
natsche pointed to the smashed windows and slit tires of his car 
parked outside his home about one mile from the jewish settlements 
army spokesmen said 20 to 30 arabs were involved in each of 
three disturbances in hebron they said the arabs erected stone 
barricades set tires ablaze and threw rocks 
according to the army account the unrest began about 11 pm 
wednesday and lasted until about 3 am at one point a jeep with 
soldiers was trapped by the rioters the army said 
in the course of the riots the lives of the soldiers were 
endangered and they were forced to shoot the area commander 
said 
three arabs were lightly wounded in the legs by army gunfire 
and two women were taken to a hospital suffering the effects of 
tear gas he said 
the army said one arab car was set ablaze but that the unrest 
was instigated by palestinian rioters not jewish settlers 
the arabrun palestine press service said israelis from the 
nearby kiryat arba settlement started to smash car windows about 
midnight and arab residents went outside to see what was happening 
the first arabs to go outside were beaten by settlers said the 
agency 
on wednesday defense minister yitzhak rabin said the armys 
efforts to curb three months of palestinian unrest have been 
hampered by the presence of jewish settlements in the occupied 
lands 
