japans unadjusted trade surplus fell in february 
from a year ago the finance ministry reported today 
the ministry said foreign sales exceeded foreign purchases by 
524 billion last month compared with a surplus of 713 billion 
in february 1987 
the february surplus was up 308 billion from january but the 
ministry said trade usually dwindles in january because of the long 
new year holiday 
imports shot up 48 percent from a year ago to a record 1496 
billion in february while exports rose 172 percent to 202 
billion the previous high for imports was 1476 billion in 
december 1987 
japans surplus in trade with the united states fell to 340 
billion from 397 billion in february 1987 exports rose 97 
percent to 681 billion dollars while us imports soared by 519 
percent to a record 341 billion 
us aircraft purchases accounted for a large portion in the 
imports totaling 47786 million up 1942 percent from a year 
earlier 
the previous monthly high for us imports was 312 billion set 
in june 1986 
