<TEXT>
fans of robin hood are up in arms and the city of 
nottingham has been accused of shooting itself in the wallet by 
putting out a tourism brochure debunking the legend of the medieval 
outlaw 
the glossy color brochure takes a skeptical academic line on 
robin hood his love affair with maid marian the existence of his 
faithful lieutenant friar tuck and that he robbed the rich to give 
to the poor 
we are not debunking anything we are putting robin hood in 
historical context insisted city council spokesman tim jones 
the city fathers have done a disservice to their own city 
countered malcolm barker of the robin hood society who took up the 
cudgels on the outlaws behalf 
barker doesnt claim that the story as handed down by 
hollywood is true he simply objects to tinkering with a beautiful 
legend that also is a major tourist attraction 
if mickey mouse can bring a fortune into florida why 
shouldnt robin hood bring a fortune in to the people of 
nottingham he said in a british radio interview 
the affair came to light thursday in londons daily telegraph in 
a report headlined robin hood is robbed of myth and romance 
the brochure undermines many of the popular notions about robin 
hood and his band of merry men not to mention his favorite woman 
maid marian it says comes from a 13th century french poem 
while chubby friar tuck is probably an amalgam of two characters 
from different parts of england 
as for robin himself the brochure notes that in the earliest 
tales he was a highwayman who robbed travelers in neighboring 
yorkshire and was in business strictly for himself 
graham black curator of nottingham castle museum and a 
historian whose work contributed to the brochure was quoted by the 
telegraph as saying one of the problems about robin hood is that 
the legend is 700 years old a story handed on by word of mouth 
and it was 200 years before people became literate 
his philanthropy was the fashionable academic interpretation 
of the 1950s black said but there is no evidence for this 
jones said in an interview that the legend took its present form 
under the 19th century victorians 
it remains a potent one when raisa gorbachev wife of the 
soviet leader visited nottingham in 1984 city officials said she 
asked about robin hood apparently regarding him as a socialist who 
believed in the redistribution of wealth 
barker the outlaws defender said does it really matter 
its an admans dream weve got something here that is 
wonderful visitors come from all over the world that know about 
robin hood and maid marian and i think that the city fathers have 
done a disservice to their own city 
nottingham a city of 290000 people in central england can 
hardly be accused of neglecting the legend its main beltway is 
called maid marian way and two rival consortiums are planning 
robin hood exhibition centers for the city 
hordes of tourists visit the sherwood forest center where they 
can see displays of medieval lifestyles and gaze at the oak tree 
where the merry men may or may not have relaxed after a hard days 
archery 
brian marshal chairman of the city tourism council that 
produced the brochure says the debate about maid marian is largely 
irrelevant people are more interested in robin hood versus the 
sheriff of nottingham he said because its always the good guy 
against the bad guy isnt it 
i think people will feel what they feel if they want to 
believe in maid marian then theyll do that he said 
</TEXT>
