<TEXT>
illinois blacks will deliver their primary vote 
almost exclusively to favorite son jesse jackson next tuesday but 
black leaders credit the monolithic vote to jacksons charisma and 
not a daleystyle political machine 
jackson who has had his differences with the black hierarchy in 
his adopted hometown of chicago doesnt need a machine to ensure 
the black vote observers say 
this is a movement vote that is bigger than the capabilities 
of any ward committeeman or political organizer said don rose a 
longtime chicago political consultant who predicts jackson will win 
up to 95 percent of the black vote in the illinois primary 
but jacksons supporters are working hard to mobilize that vote 
and more importantly to make sure supporters realize the 
necessity of also voting for jacksons slated convention delegates 
in illinois 
illinois beauty pageant primary is separate from the election 
of 173 delegates to the democratic national convention 
jackson is fielding full delegate slates in only 17 of the 
states 22 congressional districts he is one delegate short in 
four other districts and has no slate in the nearly allwhite 
suburbs on chicagos northwest side 
the black vote alone wont be enough to give jackson a victory 
in the illinois primary and may not be enough to lock up second 
place rose said 
he predicted the black vote would amount to between 23 percent 
and 25 percent of the entire democratic vote in illinois if he 
gets 10 percent of the white vote that would give him 30 percent 
and make it unlikely for him to carry the state rose said 
right now there is a tremendous fervor in the community for 
jesse after the outcome of super tuesday said chicago alderman 
