<TEXT>
a family of musicians demanding to be flown to 
london set off a bomb aboard an aeroflot jet and killed four people 
before an assault team stormed the plane and shot dead five of the 
hijackers tass said today 
the hijackers carried weapons and explosives aboard the plane in 
their instruments the official soviet news agency said in 
addition to the nine dead 20 passengers were reported injured in 
tuesdays hijacking of the tupolev154 plane tass said 
tass identified the 11 air pirates as members of a family 
musical ensemble from siberia known as the ovechkins it gave no 
information on their motives 
the hijackers set off the bomb while the plane with 76 
passengers was on the ground near leningrad tass said 
the government newspaper izvestia said one of the hijackers died 
in the explosion the newspaper said the surviving air pirates then 
killed their leader identified as their mother and that two of 
them committed suicide 
the hijackers seized the plane tuesday as it was headed to 
leningrad after a stop in the ural mountains city of kurgan the 
flight began in the siberian city of irkutsk 
tass reported the incident on wednesday but gave few details 
it was the second hijacking of a soviet domestic flight in 1 years 
us embassy spokesman richard gilbert said today that the 
embassy had been told no americans were aboard 
the sovietskaya rossiya daily reported today that the cockpit 
crew had been relayed a message from the hijackers that they were 
to proceed to london 
the pilots reported what happened to ground control tass 
said they were told that a refueling was needed to meet their 
demand and the airliner made an unscheduled landing 
tass said a special assault team boarded the plane after it 
landed and that the hijackers opened fire 
the bandits managed to set off an explosive device in the 
airliners tail section the plane caught fire the agency 
reported an air hostess and three passengers were killed as a 
result of the act of terrorism 
other passengers were evacuated but 20 were injured and were 
hospitalized tass said 
five of the 11 criminals were killed it stated without 
giving details radio moscow said the other six would be tried in 
court 
the bandits were the ovechkins a family musical group from 
irkutsk in siberia tass said eyewitnesses pointed to three 
leaders among the criminal team vasily and oleg ovechkin and 
their mother ninel ovechkin a plump fashionably dressed woman of 
over 50 
tass said they brought their weapons aboard in their instruments 
sovietskaya rossiya explained that the incident transpired over 
the course of the afternoon 
the jet which can carry up to 168 passengers took off from 
kurgan at 108 pm moscow time the paper said shortly before 3 
pm when the plane was nearing leningrads pulkovo airport one 
of the people aboard demanded that senior flight attendant tamara 
zharkaya take a note to the cockpit 
the note said we demand that you change course fly to 
london otherwise well blow up the plane along with the 
passengers the newspaper reported 
the crew kept their heads the paper said pilot valentin f 
kupriyanov calculated how much fuel was left then landed at an 
unidentified airfield near leningrad 
after landing the crew entered into negotiations with the 
bandits asking them to give up their criminal intentions and not 
to endanger passengers lives the newspaper said 
but the hijackers refused to listen it said 
several hours of negotiations had no result the newspaper 
said 
under these conditions the only decision that could be taken 
was to render the criminals harmless said sovietskaya rossiya 
radio moscow said in the shooting aboard the plane most of 
the hijackers were killed and the others were captured they are 
to be tried in court 
the last airliner hijacking attempt reported in the soviet union 
was on sept 20 1986 in the ural mountains city of ufa media 
reports said the hijackers were armed members of the internal 
security forces the reports said that five people including two 
of the hijackers were killed when authorities stormed the plane 
the others were tried and sentenced 
tuesdays hijack was at least the third fatal incident this year 
involving an aeroflot jet 
on jan 18 a tu154 crashed at the caspian port of krasnovodsk 
killing 11 and injuring at least 12 
a tu134 carrying 51 people crashed on feb 27 while landing at 
the siberian city of surgut tass said there were victims but gave 
no details 
reports on aviation accidents and disasters were rare until 
about two years ago when soviet leader mikhail s gorbachev 
embarked on a campaign for more open discussion of social and 
economic problems 
a civil aviation ministry official said in november that 
aeroflot would begin reporting all injury accidents this year 
