<TEXT>
crews delicately 
dismantled the pedalpowered plane daedalus on thursday and packed 
it up for the start of a journey to greece where the 70pound 
aircraft will attempt a record 74mile flight over the aegean sea 
pilots rolled the plane which resembles a monstrous pink 
dragonfly onto the tarmac at the dryden flight research facility 
where it sat in stark contrast to the giant 747 shuttle piggyback 
jetliner at the nasa facility 
engineers then separated the daedalus wings packed the aircraft 
into a container and loaded it into a moving van a planned 
demonstration flight was called off because of high winds in the 
mojave desert 65 miles north of los angeles 
daedalus will travel to masachusetts and will leave for athens 
aboard a c130 transport on march 23 the target date for the 
flight attempt is march 30 
the aircraft has been undergoing tests in southern california 
since october in preparation for the greek islands flight the 
route originally designed to duplicate the mythological daedalus 
route from crete to the greek mainland was changed slightly to 
ensure lighter winds 
greek mythology dictates that daedalus became the worlds first 
mortal to fly when he manufactured wings of wax and feathers 
according to the story his son icarus died because he flew too 
near the sun and the wax melted 
the daedalus was designed and built by a team of students 
faculty and alumni from mit it will be pedaled between crete and 
santorini by one of five world class bicycle racers currently in 
training 
if successful the flight could last up to seven hours and would 
break the distance record for humanpowered flight set in january 
1987 when the eagle experimental airplane flew 372 miles over the 
mojave desert 
the previous record was set in 1979 when the gossamer albatross 
crossed the english channel 
the daedalus can travel at an altitude of 15 feet with a top 
speed of 14 mph and stretches 30 feet from propeller to tail the 
pilot sits in a plastic cocoon dangling from a 112foot long 
styrofoam wing a 10foot propeller spins four feet from the 
pilots face 
when in flight the temperature in the cockpit increases 20 
degrees because of the exertion of the pilot designers feel they 
have until may 15 to make the record attempt after that the 
weather will be too hot 
the pilot will be selected by lottery 
one of those in training greg zack 26 of wilmington nc 
said he was physically prepared 
it would be a big bummer if i didnt go zack said the 
whole project has been a team thing though so no one will be 
flying alone i can live with it if im not flying it 
he added its a funny plane to fly its a lot of fun 
theres not much to it really you can look around and enjoy 
flying you arent busy with the controls 
heat and winds are the only adversaries he said if there are 
gusts more than 5 mph then you try to guess where it is going to 
take you and try to keep control zack said 
the other potential pilots are frank scioscia 27 scranton 
pa glenn tremml 28 new haven conn erik schmidt 25 boulder 
colo and kanellos kanellopoulos 30 vrahneika greece 
