<TEXT>
a jury thursday convicted a man of murder 
and arson in a grisly crime spree that left five people dead a 
verdict returned one day after a second jury in the rare dual 
trial convicted a codefendant 
one jury was selected for each defendant at the trial to save 
time and to prevent the possibility of publicity from one trial 
tainting potential jurors for a second 
carl butch campbell 28 and robert ahalt 42 were accused 
of beating three people to death in a bar in 1986 during a robbery 
then killing campbell and ahalts girlfriends the next day in the 
womens homes 
one of the women who was six months pregnant was sexually 
mutilated and forced to eat glass before she and her fetus died 
the bar and the womens homes were set afire 
it was only the second time in new york legal history that two 
juries have been called on to listen to one case and give two 
verdicts 
during the trial the defendants sat at the same table but the 
two juries sat on opposite sides of the courtroom one in a 
specially built jury box 
the juries and evidence were color coded the jury considering 
ahalts case wore blue lapel tags and campbells jury wore yellow 
tags 
most testimony involved both cases but when a witness was 
providing information that involved only one defendant the other 
jury was taken from the room the defendants testified in front of 
their own jury only 
campbell convicted thursday faces a sentence of 115 years to 
life in prison ahalt could receive up to 125 years to life 
sentencing was set for april 7 
each defendant was charged with three counts of arson five of 
intentional murder five of murder during the commission of a 
felony in this case robbery and one of murder during a sexual 
assault 
campbell was acquitted of a charge of murder during a robbery at 
the home of one of the women and both murder counts in the slaying 
of the woman at the other home ahalt was acquitted of murder 
during a sexual assault 
attorneys for both men had objected to the dual juries and said 
they would appeal the verdicts 
state supreme court justice donald mark had originally said that 
the verdicts would have to be delivered at the same time 
but four hours after the ahalt jury reached its decision 
wednesday night campbells attorney waived his clients right to 
have the verdicts announced simultaneously 
killed at dicks 43 lounge were the bars 75yearold coowner 
martha gruttadauria her sisterinlaw concetta amatore also 75 
and colin tuttle 56 a patron 
the next day dorreen grachus 28 and evelyn allen 38 were 
found slain in their homes a halfmile apart grachus campbells 
girlfriend was pregnant allen ahalts girlfriend was beaten to 
death police said 
firefighters found all five bodies during fires 
the first dual trial was held in 1984 in nassau county and 
involved two young men who were drag racing and were charged with 
criminally negligent homicide when their cars slammed into another 
car killing the driver 
that case has been appealed to the states highest court 
largely because of the dual trial format said bruce whitney a 
nassau county assistant district attorney 
