directors of both denverbased companies would create united 
artists entertainment co which would have interests in both cable 
television and motion picture theaters 
the two companies had agreed on an allstock merger shortly 
before the october stock market crash but canceled the deal soon 
after citing disagreement over the terms and uncertain market 
conditions 
