<TEXT>
the securities and exchange commission says 
new yorks antitakeover law is an unconstitutional impediment to 
interstate commerce 
the sec also contended wednesday that the statute conflicts with 
the williams act the 1968 federal law regulating corporate 
takeovers 
the agency made its arguments in a friendofthecourt brief 
filed in a suit brought by salant acquisition corp against 
manhattan industries inc one of the nations biggest makers of 
mens shirts and sportswear 
proliferation of state antitakeover laws since the supreme 
court upheld indianas takeover statute last year has heightened 
the issue of whether the federal or state governments should take 
the lead in regulating corporate takeovers 
the new york law prohibits a bidder who acquires more than 20 
percent of a companys stock from completing a takeover or other 
major business transaciton with the company for five years unless 
the bidder gets approval from the targets board of directors 
the statute gives corporate management virtual veto power over 
whether the company will be acquired sec general counsel daniel 
l goelzer wrote in the brief 
the law effectively preempts the williams act he argued 
goelzer said the structure and the legislative history of the 
williams act make it clear that congress believed thatit 
should be the shareholders the owners of the corporation who 
make the decision not the management 
the sec which regulates the nations securities markets is 
intervening in the case in us district court in manhattan on the 
side of salant 
salant a unit of salant corp another major apparel maker 
began a 95 million hostile takeover attempt of manhattan 
industries in february 
manhattan industries had sought to block the 16ashare buyout 
offer salant launched on feb 2 us district judge louis l 
stanton last week denied manhattan industries request for a court 
order blocking the tender offer but did not rule on salants 
constitutional challenge 
manhattan industries said wednesday it had entered into 
negotiations about a possible merger with salant 
the sec took a similar position when the supreme court 
considered a challenge to indianas antitakeover law last year 
but the court upheld the law 
in another current battle the sec has indicated it was 
considering whether to file briefs in suits challenging the newly 
enacted delaware antitakeover law which is structured somewhat 
similarly to new yorks law 
</TEXT>
