wang laboratories incs stock fell more than 20 
percent thursday as the company said customers were delaying 
orders cutting into the companys projected revenue and 
profitability 
wangs class b stock fell 350 a share to 1287 in 
consolidated trading on the american stock exchange 
in response to questions from securities analysts wang said it 
expected its revenue in the third fiscal quarter ending march 31 to 
be up 4 percent to 6 percent from the yearearlier level instead 
of 10 percent to 12 percent as previously projected 
wang also said it expects thirdquarter profits to be about 3 
percent of revenue instead of 3 percent to 5 percent as previously 
projected 
the lowell massbased maker of minicomputers and 
officeautomation equipment said it continues to expect to achieve 
its goals for revenue and profits for the full fiscal year 
indicating that orders expected for the third quarter will be 
recorded in the fourth quarter instead 
wang also said its new family of wang integrated image systems 
which allow users to manipulate data text and images on the same 
terminals were proceeding as planned and generating a 
higherthanexpected level of customer interest 
fred wang the president and chief executive said some of the 
slowing of orders may have come from customers doubts about the 
economic outlook which has brightened recently 
